title: Busty Ashley Youdan models skimpy bikinis in photoshoot
text:
She used to be pornstar Kendall Karson.
But it looks like Ashley Youdan is ready to make the move to modeling, if Friday's photoshoot in Malibu is any indication.
The 28-year-old ex adult actress sizzled in some very tiny two pieces over the course of the afternoon.
Aspiring starlet: It looks like Ashley Youdan is ready to make the move to modeling, if Friday's photoshoot in Malibu is any indication
Things started out relatively tame, as the brunette beauty donned a black triangle bikini top and matching bottoms for some classic swimwear poses.
Her long, dark tresses were parted on the left and styled down, and she accessorized with a 90s era choker necklace.
The vixen then steamed things up again in a mustard-coloured two piece which featured a pair of strappy bottoms that left very little to the imagination. A diamond choker also replaced the vintage number.
Having a ball! Things started out relatively tame, as the brunette beauty donned a black triangle bikini top and matching bottoms for some classic swimwear poses
Nothing fancy: Her long, dark tresses were parted on the left and styled down, and she accessorized with a 90s era choker necklace
She then must've started getting a little too warm, as she proceeded to take a dip in the frigid Pacific.
A final wardrobe change consisted of a white t-shirt and red panty combination.
Even though she again let the waves lap her lithe frame, she must've still needed to cool down, as she ended up pouring a large bottle of water onto herself.

While she has left the adult entertainment world behind, Ashley only recently settled a lawsuit against her ex boyfriend, violinist David Garrett, 35.
In her $12 million civil suit, she claimed that, beginning in 2014, Garrett forced her into rough sex that caused her to break a rib, wanted to hire a sex slave, forced her to drink his urine, had sex with transsexuals and used cocaine.
Though he filed a counter suit and insisted her accusations were baseless, the original suit, which was filed in June 2016, was reportedly settled in January for an undisclosed amount.
